- Thriller (listed categories: Dance & Electronic; Disco) is Michael Jackson’s landmark, highly produced studio album (produced by Quincy Jones) containing multiple widely known, tightly arranged tracks such as "Billie Jean," "Beat It," and "Thriller." It is famous for its polished production, layered instrumentation, and broad dynamic and tonal variety—qualities that tend to showcase the strengths of the CD format (clarity, separation, and fidelity). Thriller is also one of the best‑selling and most popular albums in history, giving it wide appeal and many recognizable tracks to enjoy on repeat.
