Raw Power is rejected not because it is inferior artistically—it is a landmark for punk and has historical significance—but because its intentionally raw, abrasive sound and narrower, genre‑specific appeal make it less aligned with the objective of maximizing a broadly enjoyable CD listening experience. In short: Thriller better matches the attributes (polished production, variety, and broad appeal) that a person who "enjoys listening to CDs very much" is likely to value when choosing a single CD to listen to.

