Evaluation and choice:
- Candidate 1 (Fleetwood Mac — album‑centric classic‑rock) hits nearly all my key boxes: warm analog production, storytelling sequencing, strong (notably female) emotive lead vocals, tight rhythm section, interlocking guitars, close multi‑part harmonies, and textured arrangements that explicitly reward start‑to‑finish listening and reveal ensemble details on repeat plays. That directly matches my stated preference for guitar‑forward, band‑centered AOR/classic‑rock with intimate but layered production and vocal harmonies.
