Why I select Fleetwood Mac and reject the piano double album:
- Fleetwood Mac embodies the precise combination I prioritize: song‑first, analog warmth, and the ensemble interplay (interlocking guitars + tight rhythm section) that produces the layered textures and harmonic depth I want to discover on repeated, start‑to‑finish listens. The presence of close multi‑part harmonies and emotionally communicative lead vocals is central to my stated taste and is a defining strength of the Fleetwood Mac description.
